            "answer_text": "Rainie Jones\u2019s tutorial on how to tag someone in an answer on Quora. Similar to social media platforms such as Instagram, to tag a person (or a space) or Quora you will be needing to type the symbol \u201c@\u201d.  After typing \u201c@\u201d you should see the search box shown above. Type in the person\u2019s Quora name where it says \u201csearch\u201d.  There should be options. Click on the correct one and you\u2019ve tagged someone in your answer/post! It should look like this: Rainie Jones You can even remove the last name by just pressing the delete key: Rainie I hope this helped educate you on how to tag someone in a Quora answer. ;) ",
